18@6@Then said the maid: "What a clever Elsie we have!" and sat down beside her and began loudly to weep over the misfortune.
20@6@The boy went down, and there sat Clever Elsie and the girl both weeping together.
24@6@Then said the boy: "What a clever Elsie we have!" and sat down by her, and likewise began to howl loudly.
27@6@Then said the mother likewise: "What a clever Elsie we have!" and sat down and wept with them.
29@6@But when he got into the cellar, and they were all sitting together crying, and he heard the reason, and that Elsie"s child was the cause, and the Elsie might perhaps bring one into the world some day, and that he might be killed by the pick-axe, if he should happen to be sitting beneath it, drawing beer just at the very time when it fell down, he cried: "Oh, what a clever Elsie!" and sat down, and likewise wept with them.
